metadata.name: PRINTERS #130
metadata.description:
Generative animated artwork made using shader feedback and pixel quantization.

PRINTERS is a study of rasterized type and bitmap imagery. It builds on the tradition of ASCII and typographic art, blending dithering techniques with chunky, pixelated glyphs. Here, the movement and blending of color is interpreted as a monochrome composition of recognizable pixel patterns taken from legacy video games and operating systems. What appears as typography is actually a custom set of 8x8 pixel patterns rendered in a GLSL shader that produces a conceptual tension between low-res graphics and high-power GPU computation.

PRINTERS is designed to be both viewed on a screen and printed on office paper with a home/office inkjet printer.

Press 'i' to invert the colors.
Press '1', '2', or '3' to scale the bitmap glyphs.
Press 'g' to download a looping animated GIF (90 frames).
Press 's' to capture a single frame.
Press 'f' (or double tap in mobile) to stretch to full screen.
Made with vanilla javascript and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: Ecos de Calma #138
metadata.description:
Through algorithms and javascript code, each artwork comes to life with unique patterns and forms, evoking a sense of inner peace. The careful selection of the color palette recreates the magic of the transition between the softness of morning or evening light, with warm and subtle tones that intertwine in harmony.

'Ecos de Calma' invites viewers to explore their own sense of serenity and find moments of calmness in contemplating these generative creations. Let yourself be enveloped by the experience and immerse yourself in the subtle nuances and harmony of each color palette, where the moon and the tree come together to create a scene of tranquility and beauty.

Features:
15 Color Palettes.
5 Canvas Sizes.
Moon: Full Moon / Waning Crescent.
One or two hills.

Press "S" to download the image.

Created by Fernando Cabral.

metadata.name: Complex World #4
metadata.description:
"Complex World" is a genesis collection on fx(hash).
In this collection, I present to you a series of generative voxel art consisting of 36 unique pieces. These artworks are created using JSplacement, a powerful tool that generates pseudo-random 8K displacement maps.
The surfaces produced by JSplacement form the basis of these generative voxel art pieces.
The random details and vibrant colors come together to create a captivating 3D space that invites you to imagine the possibilities of a connected future,
where technology and creativity intertwine to shape new realities.

software :Magicavoxel
size: 2048 x 2048
left 3
right 3
bottom 4

metadata.name: TIMEFRAMES #52
metadata.description:
‚ÄòWhat if you could take a photo of time?‚Äô

As a photographer myself, the act of taking photos is the act of freezing moments of time. Moments that will no longer ever be here. Each layer represents not only 3 aspects of time (hours, minutes and seconds) but also a very important aspect of photography: the light. Combining these two instances: the visual interpretation of light and the generative aspect of time - I present ‚ÄòTIMEFRAMES‚Äô.

12 selected colors. 5,688,900 possible combinations.

The less layers the rarer - ranging from 100% to 18%
All timeframes that have 42 on it like 4:20:00, 4:42:42, 4:20:42 are rarer - ranging from 50% to 42%
The darker the colors the rarer - ranging from 100% to 89%

Click on the image to Download. Created with @PureSpider‚Äôs template.

Florescentia is a work that has gone through several stages. I started with a foundation, depicting a nebula in space with intricate details. As I let myself be guided by the code, I drew inspiration from artworks like "Meridian" by Matt DesLauries and "Anticyclone" by William Mapan. The freedom and fulfillment I experienced in the creative process inspired me to name it Florescentia.
